<node id="Interest Rates">
  <data key="d0">Interest Rates</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Interest Rates refer to the percentage at which money can be borrowed or lent. Rising interest rates are a significant concern for investors, leading to various financial impacts such as declines in stock performance, particularly affecting sectors like technology. This rise contributes to broader market selloffs and heightened investor concerns due to increased borrowing costs and reduced liquidity in the markets.

The descriptions consistently highlight that rising interest rates exacerbate investor anxiety and precipitate market downturns across different sectors, with a notable impact on tech stocks. The overarching theme underscores the critical role of interest rate fluctuations in shaping investor behavior and market dynamics.&lt;SEP&gt;Rising interest rates are a factor contributing to the market selloff.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7504d68fad10caa1cd0ea41314ed2ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fcc4bf66788ce00c23c3e736753ea50a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-886b4b629f3088ef8656c792cf7b3e8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cdd29ae3537f38a27c3848632ad51359&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-daa296a353c26f41dfc613743d24e936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b9e37e8f7e8a98183b1724c16ce814a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9648988cb67db9843bc13754ac3d6ab6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-726c374f489423e007bce76f7810b46e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ebe784b7ece61edcdd2e054763c0ce3</data>
